To this day, I recognize in me, as a doctor and as a manager, characteristics that come from Underworld.
When I finished my internship and was debating whether to go abroad for a training period, Shaul pushed and directed me, and helped me with letters of recommendation and advice on how to conduct myself.
The training period was a very important time for my professional development, and without Shaul's support and push I'm not sure this would have happened.
On my return, when I received an offer to join the hospital board, Saul was again the one who supported and helped.
